Peachtree City Police Chief William McCollom called 911 to report accidentally shooting his ex-wife Margaret as she slept in their suburban Atlanta home early New Year's Day . 
  The shooting left Margaret paralyzed below the waist . 
  He was indicted on Wednesday on a misdemeanor reckless-conduct charge . 
  Investigators found no evidence that he intended to harm Margaret . 
  He resigned from the chief's job in March . 
 